Michelin and Fesvial together for helmet use
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, with the collaboration of the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to promote the use of the helmet, mainly among the youngest drivers, both entities reported today.
This initiative aims to raise awareness about the importance of wearing the helmet, as it is the only protective element capable of preventing head injuries or even death in the event of an accident while riding a motorcycle.
Michelin said the campaign is part of its commitment to road safety, which “goes beyond designing and manufacturing products that are safer every day” and that it also contributes to this goal through other pedagogical and informational actions.
This new campaign to promote the use of the helmet on motorcycles, under the motto 'To be or not to be', will have a first phase in which posters will be distributed in more than 500 motorcycle workshops, with the aim of achieving maximum dissemination.
Lastly, Michelin stressed that road safety “is a constant concern” for the company, since as a manufacturer of two-wheeler tyres, one of its main goals is to develop increasingly safe products.
